## How Does SEO Differ from Paid Advertising?

SEO generates organic visibility through content quality and technical optimisation, whilst paid advertising purchases immediate placement through financial bidding. SEO requires upfront investment but delivers compounding returns as authority builds. Paid advertising provides instant visibility but stops immediately when spending stops.

Most businesses benefit from combined approaches: paid advertising generates immediate leads whilst SEO builds sustainable visibility. My [semantic SEO methodology](/services/semantic-seo/) focuses specifically on organic visibility that compounds over time.

## How Long Does SEO Take?

SEO results typically appear within 3-6 months for competitive terms, though some improvements show within 4-8 weeks. Initial gains come from [technical fixes](/services/technical-seo-audit/) and quick-win optimisations. Sustained ranking improvements require consistent content publication and topical authority building over 6-12 months.

Results vary based on competition, website age, existing authority, and content quality. New websites face longer timelines than established sites adding SEO optimisation. Highly competitive industries require more comprehensive strategies than niche markets with limited competition.

